tyle=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><span style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">Date : 16th-17th September 2017.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">Location : Moksh Mantra, Khopoli-Pen road.&nbsp;</span></b><br style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">Imagine your surroundings without colour. Any colour. Not the greens, no blues and no more shades in your clothes. And what if most of these colours that you see on your fashion choices or hoardings are all deadly to the environment?&nbsp;</span><br style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">This post monsoon camping, we will add colours to your life that are all natural and guess what, they are made by you. Get your hands onto the simplest ways of making colours at home and learn how to naturally dye your clothes. Let your creativity flow amid the monsoon fresh landscape of our campsite and take back your imaginative patterns on clothes.&nbsp;</span><br style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">And t</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\" style=\"display: inline; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">hat\'s not it. With dancing under the rain and skin friendly colours made, play around as much and get yourself all clean in the water in just one go, the colours that would end up adding a shine to your face.&nbsp;<br><br><b>About the campsite :</b><br>Two hours from Mumbai, the Moksh Mantra campsite is located in Varsai area off Khopoli- Pen road. Nestled among hills, with acres of green plains spread around and a view of the mighty Manikgad, it is a site for a comfortable yet raw camping experience. With no unwanted vehicle sounds, it is the perfect excuse to reconnect with your travel-buddies and yourself!<br><br>Campsite Photo Link :&nbsp;<a href=\"https://goo.gl/photos/FqrpzZhcSscr75TU6\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" data-lynx-mode=\"async\" data-lynx-uri=\"https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fgoo.gl%2Fphotos%2FFqrpzZhcSscr75TU6&amp;h=ATOebuY9_uOJE1McjsOpFqGcgBWFyD8XaRMi8mEPbWkCBYcJJAGHEwY8ZKaKpFpgYjdA98YuW0fiH-HfrJT-fHP37F6ID_j_8UpS5LOfuOhMM4PquWxMDq0BCrMFkMkejjrknC-J-XFbzACCPOp-7CTaHTMktQpzesCYPEws1F8cmnzC\" style=\"color: rgb(54, 88, 153); cursor: pointer; font-family: inherit;\"><span style=\"font-family: inherit;\">https://goo.gl/photos/</span><wbr><span class=\"word_break\" style=\"display: inline-block; font-family: inherit;\"></span>FqrpzZhcSscr75TU6</a><br><br>Plan :&nbsp;<br>Day 1 : 16th September (Saturday)<br>11:00 am - Check in.<br><br>Reach the campsite to settle in your tents and get used to landscape around. Sit back and fill your hunger with freshly prepared lunch and gear up for playing with colours, your favorites the way you want them. Learn how to make Holi colours and naturally dye clothes at the workshop followed by fun activities at the campsite. Your delicious home-cooked dinner and a chance to barbecue marshmallows accompanies you while enjoying the weather turning cold next to the campfire.&nbsp;<br>Fall in love with everything around!<br><br>Day 2 : 17th September (Sunday)<br>Your dance floor and your colors are all set to embrace you this morning. All wet sets grounds to move around either at the dance floor or at the volleyball court – wake up to a fun-packed morning and serve your stomachs with a healthy breakfast before you head out.<br><br>11:00 am : Check out.<br><br>Cost : 2500/- Per person for Tent<br>1000/- more for bus transport from Mumbai to Mumbai.<br><br>For payment using credit/debit card/net-banking :&nbsp;<br><a href=\"https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fgoo.gl%2F9Dge3R&amp;h=ATO-QvQKhCghy_iJkh_XE8I4My3L9byWGrrnGGVgC0kGfjEpkAoOL4RRJRVn_r40Oitvx6ygynU_JJHwuENsm8nikVGNqQ_VN1r6cdTt2r4mGZ1TJzFZJWK6CJCFBOfVkXDXdeq-ZjZfYIT_r790TLjpGbXpeEUOIdMFFAVn6jwt6WvO\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" data-lynx-mode=\"async\" style=\"color: rgb(54, 88, 153); cursor: pointer; font-family: inherit;\">https://goo.gl/9Dge3R</a><br><br>Inclusions :<br>. Stay in tents (Sleeping bags and mats included)<br>. Meals: Lunch, Evening snacks, Dinner (veg/non-veg), Marshmallow Barbecue, Breakfast<br>. Home-made colour and natural dyeing workshop<br>. Campfire charges<br>. Campsite entry charges<br>. First aid box and certified first aid responders<br>. Mapping Journeys team assistance&nbsp;<br><br>Exclusions :<br>. Meals during travel<br>. Personal expenses<br>. Insurance of any kind<br>. Medical hospitalization, evacuation and related expenses<br>. Any item not covered under “inclusions”<br><br>For confirmation of the seat, full amount needs to be deposited prior to the event. Prior to making any payments please confirm about the seat availability.<br><br>Terms and Conditions and Cancellation Policy :<br><a h