rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">Matheran is a hill station, near Mumbai, in the west Indian state of Maharashtra. It’s known for its mild climate and well-preserved colonial architecture. It is famous for its various points like the Louisa point, Panorama point, One tree hill point, Monkey point, Echo point etc. A majority of these points can be reached via hiking. One such point is The Sunset Point. It is a picturesque hike which starts from the beautiful Dodhani village (famous for a 115ft waterfall, where rappelling is</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\" style=\"display: inline; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">&nbsp;conducted during monsoons) and follows the Matheran range till Dasturi naka.<br><br>Motor vehicles are banned and many visitors arrive by a narrow-gauge railway on the 1907 Neral–Matheran Toy Train.<br><br>Itinerary:<br>Train Meeting Point:<br>06:08 am: Cstm<br>06:26 am: Vadala road<br>06:37 am: Kurla<br>06:57 am: Vashi&nbsp;<br>07:28 am: Panvel, Proceed for breakfast.<br><br>(Note: People who are from Dadar/Borivali can catch train from Kurla for Panvel )<br><br>08:30 am: Start our journey to Dodhani village.<br><br>Once at Dodhani village around 9.30 am, we will be taking a short break to get to know each other via a short introduction session prior to starting the trek.<br>The time required to reach Sunset point is approximately 2 hrs. We will be reaching the Sunset point by noon. The first half hour is a flat plateau followed by a series of gradual ups and downs with only the last part being steep. It is a straight walk from Sunset point to the end of the trek.<br>After exploring the top, we will continue our trek further to Matheran market where lunch will be available for all. After lunch, a short half hour hike will take us to Dasturi point which will mark the end of our trek.<br>From Dasturi we take a cab which will drop us at Neral by 5 pm.<br>All our travellers will reach back to Mumbai by 7 pm max.<br><br>Cost: Rs.1300/- Per person.<br>Group discount applicable for a group of 3 or more.<br><br>For payment using credit/debit card/net-banking :<br><a href=\"http://go.eventshigh.com/mappingjourneys\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" data-lynx-mode=\"async\" data-lynx-uri=\"https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fgo.eventshigh.com%2Fmappingjourneys&amp;h=ATOSQkxHmALswXZ0oWYczkBdrzqzR9XYg65BYpRjdxIxPiaMB2g3OVXGEYl7wT6os73NdzYS_mnrgagXwWG7_E6GIZLMLi17LKn1h2r9REnsBHoykn-c5rUMKU_jnQgRhGVBEdkVdfFdkt2AwtRaEQulzVL2nLJxNeG7Xvrg8pvDkTUg\" style=\"color: rgb(54, 88, 153); cursor: pointer; font-family: inherit;\"><span style=\"font-family: inherit;\">http://go.eventshigh.com/</span><wbr><span class=\"word_break\" style=\"display: inline-block; font-family: inherit;\"></span>mappingjourneys</a><br><br>Do confirm about the seat availability prior to any payments!<br><br>Inclusions:<br>The cost includes,<br>. Transport from Panvel to Dodhani (public transport)<br>. Transport from Matheran to Neral (public transport)<br>. Breakfast and Evening Snacks.<br>. Entry fees.<br>. Trek charges.<br>. Safety and First aid responder.<br>. Guide and Professional Expertise.<br>. Mapping Journeys team alongwith.&nbsp;<br><br>Exclusions:<br>. Meals during travel.<br>. Personal expenses.<br>. Insurance of any kind.<br>. Medical hospitalization, evacuation and related expenses.<br>. Any item not covered under “inclusions”<br><br>Smoking and consumption of alcohol is strictly prohibited. For confirmation of the seat, full amount needs to be deposited prior to the event. Prior to making any payments please confirm about the seat availability.<br><br>Terms and Conditions and Cancellation Policy :&nbsp;<a href=\"https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fmappingjourneys.com%2Fterms_and_conditions.html&amp;h=ATO4d5eDKRinGkmy5vbVeb5Yxj40Piz124O60SQCGq-aZa00mnh8Kc8fxOXicVi6Ao8_