ar’s this time is going to be an ‘era switch’ for the newbies, those ‘born in the 90s’ would find it to be a crazy stage to go back in time, get pampered as kids and relive the 90s, without having anyone to switch off the TV or call you home early to finish homework! The liveliness of the decade calls out to engage the new generation as much as the old one through its little forgotten, lost in time elements! This NYE, be the kid and cling to the TV remotes as much, or be the time traveler sneaking into the world of 90s, gathering once again at the secluded, off the hustle, Moksh Mantra Campsite in Khopoli!</span><br style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">And like we had it last time, ‘everything continues to be fair, when y</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\" style=\"display: inline; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">ou are having fun’<br>Snaps from our last Nye:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fphotos.app.goo.gl%2FgnCtertkOtB6egel2&amp;h=ATMFyqT3U8se5WyoZI3QkzGvFUhd59yNtOQ2Qy0OCA335K8wYQR2MRa5mjLQbR0NDfDiIeGUZvPdwtlHg5EA8BAVenWW12vq9h9KT0ype2c16aCtWae-YwH2dUHStsV5JOPt-04A_FhkUX1RZN5fo8qsrEbdfsotl_3Mp6HEC7J4Wm0kFw\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" data-lynx-mode=\"async\" style=\"color: rgb(54, 88, 153); cursor: pointer; font-family: inherit;\"><span style=\"font-family: inherit;\">https://photos.app.goo.gl/</span><wbr><span class=\"word_break\" style=\"display: inline-block; font-family: inherit;\"></span>gnCtertkOtB6egel2</a>&nbsp;<br><br>Introducing to you the flavor of the 90s –<br><br>The new at the New Year’s this time is what’s lost in the era and sees no coming back. We go back in time and recreate the era of Tazos, Macarena, Mr India, Govinda, Tele Tubbies and our beloved, Tom and Jerry!<br><br>This New Year’s, you be the kid and we be your Cartoon Network,<br>you be wanting the TV remote and we be your Sunday blockbuster,<br>your Popeye and Johnny Bravo;<br>you be excited about PCs and video games, we be Daves, Mario and the 999, all installed!<br><br>You are the 90s kid and you have enjoyed a childhood none in the coming generation would ever get to see. So, celebrate yourself this New Year’s, because you are still new to the new!<br><br>And it doesn’t end there!<br>A fun-filled New Year for those who enjoy gaming and winning<br>A karaoke evening for those who love spontaneity and<br>A DJ, especially for those who believe music and memories go hand-in-hand<br><br>Plan:&nbsp;<br>31st December 2017: Reach at 7pm<br>1st January 2018: Check out at 11am<br><br>About the campsite:<br>Two hours from Mumbai, the Moksh Mantra campsite is located in Varsai area off Khopoli- Pen road. Nestled among hills, with acres of green plains spread around and a view of the mighty Manikgad, it is a site for a comfortable yet raw camping experience. With no unwanted vehicle sound it is the perfect excuse to reconnect with your travel-buddies and yourself!<br><br>Cost: 3750/-&nbsp;<br>Add 500/- for transport from Mumbai to Mumbai.<br><br>Special early bird offer: 3550/-* for tent stay.<br>*Valid only till 20th December, 10pm.<br><br>Inclusions:<br>- Stay in tent<br>- Meals: Evening snacks, Dinner (veg non veg), Breakfast, Barbecue, Breakfast<br>- Activities in the night<br>- Campfire<br>- DJ<br>- First aid and safety<br><br>Exclusions:<br>- Meals during travel.<br>- Personal expenses<br>- Insurance of any kind<br>- Medical hospitalization, evacuation and related expenses<br>- Any item not covered under “inclusions”<br><br>Smoking and consumption of alcohol is strictly prohibited. For confirmation of the 