>20 min from here you will reach the campsite<br><br>Or here is the google maps link(advised to save maps offline) :<a href=\"https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fgoo.gl%2Fmaps%2F8CC9KEvvg7P2&amp;h=ATPkJ6gYpJCHfcEblAhlNW25O9aR4ozYE8_KfiGfsLDeX1nedVAuuHgZwIpigyY0DET6skgG9Y0qhkHzqbinb5o63dZokCbGCRq74JYvtSXt1INZmMHodQ-nq0b1nr7PKw0XHuzjH16hk3varSNSbhRxOGD4fa7k5Eh63F-N6mEfahTD8i8\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" data-lynx-mode=\"async\" style=\"color: rgb(54, 88, 153); font-family: inherit;\"><span style=\"font-family: inherit;\">https://goo.gl/maps/</span><wbr><span class=\"word_break\" style=\"display: inline-block; font-family: inherit;\"></span>8CC9KEvvg7P2</a></span><br></p>','2018-02-17 00:00:00',1400,'https://scontent.fbom2-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/26908098_1260959487337936_3415957472464234653_n.jpg?oh=f4d84d532d98403d9ed1e55dbad36963&oe=5AE77E2A',0),(26,'The highest peak of West Bengal - Sandakphu!','<p><span style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">Four of the five highest peaks in the world, Everest, Kangchenjunga, Lhotse and Makalu can be seen from its summit.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">Sandakphu or Sandakfu (3636 m; 11,941 ft) is the highest peak in the state of West Bengal, India. It is situated at the edge of the Singalila National Park in Darjeeling district on the West Bengal-Nepal border, and is the highest point of the Singalila Ridge. Sandakphu has a small village on the peak with few hostels.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">If luck favors you, the panoramic view of the mighty Himalayas will be at your sight.&nbsp;</span><br style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><span style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">Date : 14th - 18th April 2018!</span><br style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">Height : 3636 mt (11941ft).</span></b><br style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">Route : Maneybhanjang - Chitrey - Tumling - Kalipokhri- Sandakphu - Rimbik.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">Photo album link :&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fgoo.gl%2Fphotos%2FmR61LFpSU8KD6kbK6&amp;h=ATM_VtizhNiBvvMI1iLRie-pqHF2jWFCD08pazF-T21EdTA7Crsz_6weuwmnZzUDcUXJrZegK0X2b5ognyJtGtP4Lyr6ACLLW1tFyC3-jhM0PocyaKNGx6arwsMyzGs35PI7KDNw1L9sDvtHN_VPxiWJ9tlpn4Ed552mtk_EcGL5xDaOfsk\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" data-lynx-mode=\"async\" style=\"color: rgb(54, 88, 153); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span style=\"font-family: inherit;\">https://goo.gl/photos/</span><wbr><span class=\"word_break\" style=\"display: inline-block; font-family: inherit;\"></span>mR61LFpSU8KD6kbK6</a><span class=\"text_exposed_show\" style=\"display: inline; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><br><br>Brief Itinerary : Day 0 : Receiving at NJP (New Jalpaiguri) station or Bagdogra airport (16kms from NJP). A 4hr drive will take us to our base camp Maneybhanjang. The cost of reaching till the base camp to be shared by the travellers.We will arrange for jeeps to reach base camp.<br><br><b>Day 1 : 14th April : Maneybhanjang to Chitrey in Jeep followed by Trek till Tumling.<br>Day 2 : 15th April : Tumling - Kalipokhri Trek.<br>Day 3 : 16th April : Kalipokhri - Sandakphu Trek.<br>Day 4 : 17th April : Sandakphu - Rimbik Trek.<br>Day 5 : 18th April : Rimbik - NJP Station (Till Afternoon).</b><br><br>Detail Itinerary :&nbsp;<br>Day 1 : We will be starting our journey till the top by taking our jeeps further till Chitrey (8340ft). A small Buddhist monastery awaits at Chitrey, we will take it easy, halt for a while, and start our trekking marathon. The day will end at Tumling. Trekking from Chitrey till Tumling which is approximately 11km and takes around 5-6 hrs. Our day ends at Tumling and the magical view of the famous Sleeping Buddha.<br><br>Distance covered today : 13km.&nbsp;<br>Maneybhanjang - 6600ft.<br>Tumling - 9842ft.<br><br>Day 2 : Say good morning to the mighty Kanchenjunga and its neighbours in the view.<br><br>Today we move from Tumling towards the famous Singalila national park followed by Gairibas and finally to Kalipokhri. Kali means black and Pokhri stands for water area. The village name is so derived, the water is black not due to pollution but because the pond is very muddy and hence the water never freezes. Kalipokhri lies 6 kms away from Gairibas, approximately 3.5hrs is required to reach Kalipokhri from Tumling.<br><br>Distance covered today : 13km.<br>Tumling - 9842ft.<br>Kalipokhri - 10196ft.<br>Kalipokhri!<br><br>Day 3 : Today the enthusiasm will be doubled as we will be trekking right up till Sandakphu covering roughly 6 kms which requires 3 hrs approximately. We will start early morning to make sure that we get to see the snow peaks twice, once when we reach Sandakphu and again before leaving from Sandakphu.<br>On route we will be coming face up with Bhikeybhanjang (2km from Kalipokhri, the name literally means \"Valley of poison\" because of the poisonous Aconite plants that grow in abundance here.) Sandakphu peak can be seen from Kalipokhri itself. Get ready for the steepest climb starting from Bhikeybhanjang right till Sandakphu. This 4 kms trek can easily take up 2.5hrs. Finally, after trekking for 2 days, we will reach SANDAKPHU - THE HIGHEST POINT OF WEST BENGAL.<br><br>Distance covered today : 6km.<br>Kalipokhri - 10196ft.<br>Sandakphu - 11941ft.<br><br>Day 4 : Today we start moving towards Rimbik.<br><br>The most popular return route from Sandakphu is via Gurdum to Srikhola and then to Rimbik. The trail descends through the dense Singalila forest full of oaks and chestnuts. There are some places where even sunlight can\'t enter. You will find lots of flowering rhododendron trees on the way that bloom in April and May.&nbsp;<br><br>This is one of the shortest routes. The stretch from Sandakphu up to Gurdum is 10kms and can be covered in about 3.5 hours. Gurdum is a picture perfect tiny village.<br><br>The village is surrounded by dense forests. If you are lucky, you can even see animals like Himalayan bears.<br><br>In about 1.5 hours walk from Gurdum, you will reach another beautiful place called Srikhola. The place has been named after a lovely mountain stream which too has the same name (the word khola means a stream). From here, Rimbik is another 7kms away(3 hours from Srikhola), stay there overnight and take early morning shared jeep back to NJP/Airport.<br><br>Distance covered today : 19km.&nbsp;<br>Sandakphu - 11941ft.<br>Rimbik - 7498ft.<br>Enroute Sandakphu!<br><br>Day 5 : Share jeep till NJP Station/Bagdogra airport.<br><br>Cost : Rs. 11500/- per person.(Group discount applicable for two or more)<br>Block your seats in advance by paying 5000rs Non Refundable.<br><br><b>Cost inclusions :&nbsp;</b><br><span style=\"font-family: inherit;\">. All food (Lunch,Tea,Dinner,Breakfas</span><wbr><span class=\"word_break\" style=\"display: inline-block; font-family: inherit;\"></span>t)<br>. A local guide<br>. All Stay charges (All attached washrooms except at Kalipokhri and Sandakphu)<br>. Jeep costs (Manebhanjang - Chitrey)<br>. Entry and Guide fees<br>. Safety and First aid<br>. Singalila enrty fee&nbsp;<br>. Mapping Journeys traveller alongwith (first aid certified)<br><br><b>Exclusions :</b><br>. Travel from till Maneybhanjang<br>. Personal Expenses<br>. Camera Charges<br>. Tips / Mineral Water / Beverages<br>. Insurance of any kind. Medical and Evacuation Charges<br>. Cost incidental to any change in the itinerary/ stay on account of flight cancellation due to bad weather, ill health, roadblocks and/or any factors beyond control<br>. Anything not included under \"inclusions\"&nbsp;<br><br>For confirmation of the seat, full amount needs to be deposited prior to the event.&nbsp;<br><br>Payment options: *Do confirm about the seat availability prior to any payments.*<br><br>-Neft/Imps:<br>Bank Name: HDFC<br>Name: Mapping Journeys Pvt Ltd<br>Account type: Current account&nbsp;<br>Account No: 50200019713035<br>IFSC Code: HDFC0000582<br>Branch: Thakur village, Kandivali<br><br>-Paytm Number: 9867697306<br><br>Terms and Conditions and Cancellation Policy:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fmappingjourneys.com%2Fterms_and_conditions.html&amp;h=ATOLLxX88k4qdsfU9IjT_WWlsarzL1JZkqeJH_VTazPeKKDpuluyvPSk3Ea1UAt1hYPTNWi9tk9nPK-ry8Dz1X669ZzgcQxHuW-6iFdiwq48d3nknCCWNWqLyRwVftuBHmFU5RnSSzdOyH2jG9f1i4n0yX0s8_k1ETjSrxsjg81yaGkMB2k\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" data-lynx-mode=\"async\" style=\"color: rgb(54, 88, 153); font-family: inherit;\"><span style=\"font-family: inherit;\">http://</span><wbr><span class=\"word_break\" style=\"display: inline-block; font-family: inherit;\"></span><span style=\"font-family: inherit;\">mappingjourneys.com/</span><wbr><span class=\"word_break\" style=\"display: inline-block; font-family: inherit;\"></span>terms_and_conditions.html</a><br><br>Website:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.mappingjourneys.com%2F&amp;h=ATMTiUhYwg0mVLIR7DPiOI4E1xTBkUeYiSlXj_G5SkbNnBhE3JgQfCRk2F216S6C1DLqlnzLm3XFXD96buAwXK02442_unnTxEPWHH4rz57S7cTtc5kHV9hAj3JwuGdsTQxr_mbDCjST4isEvLkNe_pZlSypu4WKZYdnHiK0s-UG0nhrj-k\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" data-lynx-mode=\"async\" style=\"color: rgb(54, 88, 153); font-family: inherit;\">www.mappingjourneys.com</a>&nbsp;<br>Like us on facebook:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/mappingjourneys/\" rel=\"nofollow\" style=\"color: rgb(54, 88, 153); font-family: inherit;\"><span style=\"font-family: inherit;\">https://www.facebook.com/</span><wbr><span class=\"word_break\" style=\"display: inline-block; font-family: inherit;\"></span>mappingjourneys/</a><br><br>For other payment options, queries and registration, please contact:<br>+91 9867693107<br>+91 9867697306<br>travel@mappingjourneys.com<br><br>HOW TO REACH NJP?<br>Flight till Bagdogra airport followed by jeep till Maneybhanjang.<br>or<br>We can help in booking train/flight tickets provided you let us know in advance. For more information on this do contact us on the given numbers.</span><br></p>','2018-04-14 00:00:00',11500,'https://scontent.fbom2-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/23168049_1193688507398368_4079015939781278280_n.jpg?oh=2586c8c2d0e8e4b2e467cc4b9c4a19b0&oe=5AEA3366',0),(27,'The God Pool - Lake Bhrigu Trek!','<p><span style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b>The God Pool - Lake Bhrigu Trek!</b></span><br style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><span style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">Dates: 22nd May to 27th May 2018 (Delhi to Delhi)</span><br style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"></b><span style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">Photo link:&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fbit.ly%2F2DANXCK&amp;h=ATMmqSsqmi4daqzhqIyjatBh-MhySe1Ab78wkvDfV0I7w5SPYgVo1VP77v7mvZ1a0LwU0OpCD3YVl5tq8tP3m1BrHTEIdR8CfWTj25_ZKnQLJNYEHZoc-TPGFkDeDOowFbb4QA3RdBhjCAgKMuoLu0_r_axmPPfEpvCwV-bdtW_jOcL5zm0\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" data-lynx-mode=\"async\" style=\"color: rgb(54, 88, 153); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">http://bit.ly/2DANXCK</a><span style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">&nbsp;</span><br style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">Any high altitude lake is a crowd puller and Bhrigu is no exception. It\'s located at a height of 4,300 metres (14,100 ft) in Kullu district, Himachal Pradesh, India.It is located to the east of the Rohtang Pass and is around 14 kilometres from Gulaba village. The lake can be reached by trek from Gulaba village. The lake is named after Maharishi Bhrigu, one of the seven great sages (Saptarshis).</span><br style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">Any high altitude trekking requires some basic pre preparation. Bhrigu is on the moderate side in terms of difficulty and can be done even by a first timer who has done some pre preparation prior to th</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\" style=\"display: inline; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(75, 79, 86); font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">e trek.You can start two weeks prior by running/jogging daily, it\'s the best training one can take to be more prepared for any high altitude treks.<br><br><b>BRIEF ITINERARY:<br>Day 1- 22nd May: Departure from Delhi by 5 PM for Manali.<br>Day 2- 23rd May: Reporting at Rumsu base camp. Acclimatization walk and Orientation for the trek.<br>Day 3- 24th May: Drive to Gulaba and trek to Rohlikohli.<br>Day 4- 25th May: Trek to Bhrigu Lake.<br>Day 5- 26th May: Descend to Gulaba and Departure from Manali.<br>Day 6- 27th May: Arrival at Delhi by 7 AM.</b><br><br>DETAILED ITINERARY:<br>Day 1: Departure from Delhi by 5 PM for Manali.<br>Participants have to board their bus from R K Ashram Marg, New Delhi at 5:00pm. Make sure your train/flight arrives in Delhi before 2:00 pm so there is enough buffer time to board your bus. Meals are not covered during bus travel.<br><br>Day 2 : Reporting at Rumsu base camp and Acclimatization walk.<br>All the participants will report at Rumsu base camp by 8 AM and will undergo registration process. Freshening up and breakfast will happen at the base camp. Post breakfast we will go for an acclimatization walk.<br>Lunch at 1 PM. Post lunch orientation. Orientation will cover all the general instructions that could be helpful for the trek like backpacking, marching technique and medical awareness. Post snacks we will have an ice breaking session.<br>Overnight stay at Rumsu base camp.&nbsp;<br><br>Day 3: Drive to Gulaba and trek to Rohlikohli.<br>After morning breakfast we will start with a beautiful jeep ride to Gulaba. The trek commences from Gulaba towards Rohlikohli camp site. The 5 to 6 hours ascend till Rohlikohli is moderate. There are two streams on the route towards the camp site (Chor Nallah and Kohli Nallah). Rohli Kohli is a beautiful camp site and offers amazing views of Solang Valley. Overnight camp at Rohli Kohli.<br><br>Day 4: Trek to Bhrigu Lake<br>Trek commences early in the morning by 7 am after breakfast, for Bhrigu Lake. It takes around 4 hours to reach to Bhrigu Lake. Packed lunch will be done at Bhrigu Lake. Care should be taken that no littering happens over here. As per the myths, Rishi Bhrigu meditated here and used to take bath in the holy water. We will then start for the descend to Rohlikohli camp site. Overnight stay in tents at Rohlikohli camp site.<br><br>Day 5: Descend to Gulaba and Departure from Manali<br>We will start with descend this morning for Gulaba. The descend is easy and takes around 3-4 hours. Departure will be done from Manali bus stand at 5 PM for New Delhi.<br><br>Day 6: Arrival at Delhi by 8 AM.<br><br>Cost: Rs.9400/- (Inclusive of GST) (Delhi to Delhi)<br><br>For payment using credit/debit card/net-banking:<br><a href=\"https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fgo.eventshigh.com%2Fmappingjourneys&amp;h=ATP7UTM1Fml5yx0UIyzGzyAaI0OdDxOCa0pJ6sj3LC2AYoae5oLWMbwd4iXtaKur6IWQhwfMHuFKsWTBfr2zAkT-O357gUiuxDgeunExprdjjM6rhQgWu8A75dHIGwmtBGDV4gBUifWLPLOaqreH8vUhqO19WUhYJhcePrr5h7x5z7jIA58\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" data-lynx-mode=\"async\" style=\"color: rgb(54, 88, 153); font-family: inherit;\"><span style=\"font-family: inherit;\">http://go.eventshigh.com/</span><wbr><span class=\"word_break\" style=\"display: inline-block; font-family: inherit;\"></span>mappingjourneys</a><br><br>Inclusions:&nbsp;<br>. Stay(Tent stay)<br>. Sleeping bag.<br>. Sleeping mat.<br>. Meals(Breakfast, Lunch, Snacks, Dinner).<br>. Professional guide.<br>. Forest permit.<br>. Personnel Insurance.<br>. Rucksack(65 liters) with cover.<br>. Plate and Mug<br>. Trekking stick and Gaiters<br>. Safety and first aid responder<br>. Trek charges<br>. All equipments rental<br>. Mapping Journeys team alongwith<br><br>Exclusions:&nbsp;<br>. Meals during travel<br>. Personal expenses<br>. Insurance of any kind<br>. Medical hospitalization, evacuation and related expenses<br>. Any item not covered under “inclusions”<br><br>GENERAL INSTRUCTIONS:<br>-Stay for male and female are separate throughout the program.<br>-Medical certificate, duly signed by MBBS doctor, is mandatory for participating in all the events.<br>-Participation in any of the Himalayan trekking program require a level of fitness. One who is participating in any of such events should do a minimum of two weeks of preparation.<br>-Trekking shoes is compulsory.<br>-Participants should check “Things to Carry list” which includes all personal clothing and other trekking accessories. Additionally we will be mailing the list as well.<br>-Smoking and drinking are strictly prohibited.<br>-Buying drugs or any illegal material is strictly prohibited. Participant found in possession of any of such items, will be detained and handed over to government authority.<br>-Instructions from Guide should be strictly followed.<br>- For confirmation of the seat, full amount needs to be deposited prior to the event. Prior 