normal;\">Gurdum, nestled in the lap of Himalayas is a small hamlet located in the Singalila National Park. Our stay will be at \"Gurdum Backpackers\' Camp\" where they have the option of staying inside a campers van/tents/homestay.&nbsp;</span><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">Day 1 : 21st October: 11km trek from Gurdum(8000ft) to Tumling(9842ft).</span><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">Day 2 : 14km trek from Tumling(9842ft) - Kalipokhri(10196ft).</span><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">Day 3 : 06km trek from Kalipokhri(10196ft) - Sandakphu(11941ft).</span><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">Day 4 : 21km trek from Sandakphu(11941ft) - Phalut Trek(11794ft).</span><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">Day 5 : 16km trek from Phalut(11794ft) - Gorkhey/Samanden(7546ft).</span><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">Day 6 : 14km trek from Gorkhey/Samanden(7546ft) - Timburey(6600ft).&nbsp;</span><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">Day 7 : 27th October: 03km trek from Timburey(6600ft) - Sirikhola Bridge(6260ft)</span><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><span style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">Detail Itinerary :&nbsp;</span><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"></b><span style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><u>Day 1 :</u> Day 1 begins with a 11km trek from Gurdum till Tumling.Trekking till Tumling takes around 5-6 hrs. Our day ends at Tumling and the magical view of the eternal Sleeping Buddha made possible by the mystic Kanchenjunga range.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><u>Day 2 :</u> Today we move from Tumling towards the famous Singalila national park followed by Gairibas and finally to Kalipokhri. Kali means black and Pokhri stands for water area. Kalipokhri lies 6 kms away from Gairibas, approximately 3.5hrs is required to reach Kalipokhri from Tumling.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><u><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"></u><span style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><u>Day 3 :</u> Today the enthusiasm will be doubled as we will be trekking right up till Sandakphu covering roughly 6 kms which requires 3 hrs approximately. Sandakphu peak can be seen from Kalipokhri itself. Get ready for the steepest climb starting from Bhikeybhanjang right till Sandakphu. This 4 kms trek can easily take up 2.5hrs. Finally, after trekking for 3 days, we will reach SANDAKPHU - THE HIGHEST POINT OF WEST BENGAL.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><u>Day 4 :</u> The marathon 21km of trekking begins today. Though a lengthy trek majority of the distance is at the same height making the trek comparatively less difficult and making Phalut the second highest peak of West Bengal.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">One of the best views of the Himalayas is seen from here.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">Phalut also has the best sunrise throughout the whole trek. It offers incredible twilight views as well in the morning from the view point.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><u>Day 5 :</u> Descending down 4200ft, today we will reach Gorkhey after a 3hrs and 11km trek. Gorkhey, a beautiful valley in the border of West Bengal and Sikkim.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">This place is situated right in between the mountains with the flowing Sirikhola river to compliment it. Take a walk down the river side to take a dip.&nbsp;</span><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">or</span><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">Descending down 4000ft, today we will reach Samanden after a 3hrs and 11km trek. It\'s the 2nd Switzerland of India, the meadows of Samanden are a treat to a trekkers eyes. The route from Gorkhey cuts through dense pine forest offering incredible experience.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><u>Day 6 :</u> A 3hr hike today will take you to a lesser know village called as Timburey. In this village there are only 6 houses. The village is surrounded by a panoramic 360 degree view of the mountains and the amazing sound of the Shrikhola river. You will find peas,potato,mustard fields all around. The Sirikhola river is just 5 min walk away.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">Our stay here will be with a Buddhist Tamang family that runs a small yet amazing homestay for the trekkers.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">Have the millet-based local beer here called as Tongba and some amazing food cooked by the family.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><u>Day 7 :</u> The easiest of all the days, today we trek for just 3km to reach our pick up point which will be the Sirikhola hanging bridge. Walking on this bridge is scary and fun both at the same time. Our jeeps will be waiting on the other side of the bridge which will take us back to NJP/Airport.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">Cost : Rs. 12250/- per person. (Excluding 5% gst)</span><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">Block your seats in advance by paying 5000rs Non Refundable.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b>Cost inclusions :</b></span><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\">. All food (Lunch,Tea,Dinner,Breakfast)</span><br style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-seri